<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How much oil replaces butter in baking?", answer: "Use 3/4 the amount of oil to replace butter. For example, if a recipe calls for 1 cup of butter, use 3/4 cup of oil. The texture may be slightly different since butter contains water and milk solids." },
  { question: "Can I substitute whole wheat flour for all-purpose flour?", answer: "You can replace up to 75% of all-purpose flour with whole wheat flour. Using 100% whole wheat will produce denser, heavier baked goods. Start with a 50/50 blend for best results." },
  { question: "How do I make a flax egg?", answer: "Mix 1 tablespoon of ground flaxseed with 3 tablespoons of water. Let it sit for 5 minutes until it becomes gel-like. One flax egg replaces one regular egg." },
  { question: "Can I use honey instead of sugar in baking?", answer: "Use 3/4 cup of honey for every 1 cup of sugar. Reduce other liquids in the recipe by 1/4 cup per cup of honey used, and lower the oven temperature by 25 degrees F to prevent over-browning." },
  { question: "What is the best egg substitute for binding?", answer: "For binding, flax eggs and chia eggs work best. For moisture, applesauce or mashed banana are excellent. For leavening, use 1/4 tsp baking soda + 1 tbsp vinegar per egg." }
]) %>

